KW  - E52
KW  - money
KW  - business cycles
KW  - shock transmission
KW  - inflation dynamics
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0022-2879
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1538-4616.2011.00388.x
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - We study the contribution of money to business-cycle fluctuations in the United States, the United Kingdom, Japan, and the euro area using a small-scale structural monetary business cycle model. Constrained likelihood-based estimates of the parameters are provided and time instabilities analyzed. Real balances are statistically important for output and inflation fluctuations. Their contribution changes over time. Models giving money no role provide a distorted representation of the sources of cyclical fluctuations, of the transmission of shocks, and of the events of the last 40 years.
ER  - 

TY  - JOUR
T1  - Deconstructing a Mortgage Meltdown: A Methodology for Decomposing Underwriting Quality
AU  - ANDERSON, CHARLES D.
AU  - CAPOZZA, DENNIS R.
AU  - VAN ORDER, ROBERT
Y1  - 2011/06/01
PY  - 2011
